sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1463000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Recombinase Switch With GFP and RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Switch synthesised by IDT from a given sequence, RFP and GFP are from the 2014 distribution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A recombinase switch with GFP one side of the switch and RFP on the other.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rev promot
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesised by IDT Technologies from a given sequence. Did not come from any genomic sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No special design considerations other than ensuring the promoter was in reverse.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rev RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesised by IDT Technologies from a given sequence. Does not come from genomic sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No specific design considerations other than ensuring that the sequence was in reverse.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: spacer
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesised by IDT Technologies from a given sequence. Sequence is not from genome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BamHI and HindIII sites contained when combined with scar sequences in switch, part BBa_K1463000. This spacer is required for the function of this larger part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Created this part with 2 restriction sites when combined with scar sites in larger composite part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: attP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthesised by IDT technologies from a given sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: attB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sythesised by IDT Technologies from a given sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Beth Greig

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rev RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Incorporated upstream of our reversed rfp part BBa_K1463520 by PCR using the primer Suffix-rfp-5??? aaccaaaaCTGCAGCGGCCGCTACTAGTATTAGGGAGGTCTCTAGTAATGGCTTCCTCCGAAGACGTTATC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Reverse ribosome binding site designed using the Salis ribosome binding site calculator to have a strength of 12,204 when placed downstream of the reversed rfp part BBa_K1463520
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There was a previous reverse RBS designed by the Edingburgh 2007 iGEM team (BBa_I742130). This had a predicted RBS strength of 495 according to the Salis RBS calculator website. We wanted a stronger reverse RBS closer in strength to BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sean Colloms
